overview: The user initiated a request for comprehensive browser-based testing
  of the sleep questionnaire application. The assistant began by checking the
  development server and navigating the application. It systematically tested
  the questionnaire's progression, initially encountering some confusion with
  navigation and snapshot timing, but eventually confirming the flow. A key
  decision was to utilize a "Pre-fill & Jump to Report (Dev)" button to expedite
  testing of the report generation and PDF download functionality, which both
  worked as expected. The assistant also tested the admin login, verifying that
  it correctly handled invalid credentials. Furthermore, it confirmed that admin
  API endpoints are protected by authentication and that the public-facing form
  submission API provides robust validation for incomplete data. The overall
  outcome was a successful validation of core application functionalities and
  API behaviors.
